					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/natvoltaic" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2800867); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2800867&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610225122" alt="NatVoltaic" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2800867)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/natvoltaic" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2800867); return false;" >NatVoltaic</a></span> <span class="odate time_1503328362 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">21 Aug 2017 15:12</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3575373">
									

<p>I haven't read any of the other Anderson Robotics tales, but this still managed to be bittersweet and sad. The length was also perfect for achieving that, and I'm impressed that something so emotional could be done in such a short tale.</p>
<p>+1</p>

							</div>

								
					
