					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/rjb-r" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1229263); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1229263&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610225122" alt="RJB_R" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1229263)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/rjb-r" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1229263); return false;" >RJB_R</a></span> <span class="odate time_1503414755 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">22 Aug 2017 15:12</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3576288">
									

<p>Hm. I really like a lot of the back and forth, but I just feel like it didn't really sell the emotional aspect to me. Maybe it's intentional because robot but Hector just came off as too cold for me to really feel like he cared about the family he lost. Conwell has a little more color but his behavior feels a little incongruous with his surroundings. There is some nice imagery here, though, making good use of the world you've crafted with AR.</p>
<p>Neutral vote.</p>

							</div>

										<div class="signature">
					<hr class="signature-separator"/>
					

<p><em>Whether you like it or not, history is on our side. We will bury you!</em></p>

